OL,3,CValdo Calocane kicked officer after
OL,4,Ckilling three people, inquiry hears
OL,6,FLouisa Hagan, who was a manager with
OL,7,Fcommunity forensic services from
OL,8,FNottinghamshire Healthcare NHS
OL,9,FFoundation Trust (NHFT), emailed a
OL,10,Fcolleague at the trust saying: "Let me
OL,11,Fknow if he (Calocane) is known to
OL,12,Fservices as obviously this is a big
OL,13,Fworry for the trust."
OL,15,FAsked by Julian Blake KC, counsel to
OL,16,Fthe inquiry, to explain her comment,
OL,17,FMs Hagan said: "Because of the media
OL,18,Finterest in this, it would need
OL,19,Fescalating.
OL,26,@rD@`OUuD@UO]yD@POU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1773846665
OL,3,CValdo Calocane kicked officer after
OL,4,Ckilling three people, inquiry hears
OL,6,F"There would be the need to involve
OL,7,Fsenior leaders as early as possible so
OL,8,Fit was about escalating that process."
OL,10,FCalocane was discharged by the trust
OL,11,Fto his GP in September 2022, which was
OL,12,Fidentified as an error in a report by
OL,13,Fthe Care Quality Commission.
OL,15,FThe inquiry heard that when Ms Hagan
OL,16,Ffound out that Calocane had been in
OL,17,Fcontact with NHFT's services before,
OL,18,Fshe responded by email: "Oh dear".
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@fO]zD@YOUzD@aO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1773846665
OL,3,CValdo Calocane kicked officer after
OL,4,Ckilling three people, inquiry hears
OL,6,FMs Hagan told the inquiry: "I think
OL,7,Fthat 'oh dear' was a reflection of the
OL,8,Fsadness of the situation.
OL,10,FMr Blake said: "It might be suggested
OL,11,Fby some that it is a concern for the
OL,12,Ftrust and their reputation."
OL,14,FMs Hagan responded: "I appreciate
OL,15,Fthat's how it may sound, but reading
OL,16,Fit now, it does make me feel sad when
OL,17,FI read it, so that's my understanding
OL,18,Fof how it was when I sent it."
OL,20,FThe inquiry continues.
OL,26,@nD@\OUrD@POUtD@\O]vD@UOUzD@^O]
